    "en": {
      "title": "\"Donier 228\" is a start of Lanka India support",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Ranil Wickramasinghe said that India's delivery of a Donier aircraft to the Sri Lankan Air Force is a good start in the maritime security cooperation between the two countries.",
        "The President said that receiving such an aircraft is an improvement for the Sri Lanka Air Force and said that it is the beginning of a great cooperation between the Sri Lanka Air Force, the Sri Lanka Navy and the Indian Navy on maritime survival.",
        "Yesterday (15) the official handing over of the maritime surveillance aircraft granted by the Government of India for Sri Lanka's maritime surveillance activities to the Government of Sri Lanka was done under the chairmanship of Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe.",
        "The Donier 228 type maritime surveillance aircraft was presented to Sri Lanka at the Katunayake Air Force Base.",
        "Further commenting there, the President said that he is thankful to India for helping Sri Lanka for a long time."
      ],
